Pleopods (
Fig. 5
): uniarticulated; male and female pleopods 1–5 with 14–29 modified attenuated setae on anterior surface, lateral, distomedial, and distal margins, the attenuated setae on distal margins reaching to anterior margins of adjacent posterior somites, 1 setulose seta on distolateral margin, pseudobranchial lobe with 4 sometimes minutely setulose setae; pleopod 1 short and subtriangular with most attenuated setae on truncate distal margin, succeeding pleopods becoming more elongate posteriorly with most attenuated setae on anterior surface, distomedial, and distal margins.
